sec.p:
The experimental setup is shown in Figure 1. It includes the following:
A tube filled with hydrogel (1);
Membranes (2) and (3), which separate the working material from the low-molecular-weight salt solutions used;
A volume (4) filled with a low-molecular-weight salt solution;
A buffer volume (5), which collects the low-molecular-weight salt that has passed through the hydrogel layer;
Electrodes (6), intended for measuring the dynamic potential difference;
A precision voltmeter (7), allowing measurements on the order of millivolts.
